topics.body:
They should make a new genre for fiction called "fictional fiction". Basically, the genre involves a certain fiction inside the story instead of the world itself. An example would be .hack, where the character, already fictional, is stuck in a video game which from his point of view, is fictional.

So, it's fourth wall breaking but not our fourth wall.
